_________________________________________
_Great for bigger servers. 20-64 players_

ZM_GARGANTUA
Made by GARGANTUA 

Story
Streets are quiet. Buildings are abandoned. Basements are empty. Everybody fled or is still hiding indoors from the zombie invasion that is now happening in the center of the city. But it was barely a month ago that the ‘virus’ began to spread at the outskirts of the city. The infection was spread throughout the country in just a short matter of time. 

A week ago, the government deployed armed forces in the city. Sightings of combat have been spotted near the train station (my other map ze_rooftop_runaway1) a few days ago. But the sound of gunfire quickly reduced. The people in the city assumed that the military was overrun by the endless hordes of zombies. So probably the military got ripped apart or they have become zombies too…..it’s now up to the civilians to rescue themselves. It is time to make a stand! Luckily for you, the military left weapons and ammunition throughout the city. 

Objective
You are one of the last civilians who stayed behind. You were counting on the military to clean up this mess but it’s a high probability that the government abandoned this city and their soldiers. You know your home is no longer safe. Food is running short so it’s time to get out and make a last stand. Kill as much zombies as you can! Everything is possible now so make smart use of the rooftops to stay ahead of the zombies. But beware, the zombies aren’t the only danger surrounding you. While you’re on the rooftops, you will face great heights so you better don’t fall down! You must survive!


My comments
This is a VERY PERSONAL map! It's actually my living area. You can even enter my appartment (the room with GARGANTUA poster, 4th screenshot is my house). I've modeled as accurate as I could. The actual real environment looks different. I just liked to give it a city 17 feeling to it. Anyway, that's why I called it zm_gargantua. 

Credits: Deathadder, Reflax,  Neox, Toby, Mats, Nikooo777 (all great members of i3D community)
Special thanks to: 
Krassell (for making the awesome secret weapon!!)
Freeze, Kaemon666 and Makaroonivelli (for help on optimizing!)
i3D (for the great ZM servers and support)

Map info
* 64 spawnplaces
* Multiple routes throughout the whole map
* Use gutterpipes of buildings to climb on rooftops!!
* Small customised weapons:
- 1 shotguns with 500 rounds
- 1 AWP's with 99 rounds
* One secret weapon: find it and glory will be yours :-)
* Custom textures: my spray offcourse! You can't miss the 'gargantua' building

Welcome to my new zombie map, zm_gameshow please leave some feedback and enjoy!

I wanted to make a zombie map with new ideas and many different ways to play.  Check out the laser room, the jumping room, the breakable concrete room, the barricading room, and the obstacles built specifically for interesting gameplay.  

Theme:  In the future we have harnessed the zombie mutation.  We take criminals or volunteers and put up to 50 into a controlled facility with many obstacles.  One is infected and then the humans and zombies fight to the death, all while being televised.

Special thanks to anyone that helped with questions and the people who tested this.

This is a map based on looking good and being balanced for game play. It's fully optimized for the OB engine (in light of my first version). It has a good selection of soundscapes, lighting effects and breakable walls/floors that give zombies a balanced playthrough with those who can make impossible to break barricades. There are several areas to hide, barricade, and camp, each with it's pro and con scenario. There is a power console which can be broken to darken the interior, which also causes several things within the map to disable and several other effects. 

________________

The map includes two secretes, A combination to the floodgates to flood the underground, and a secret room. The secret room cannot be used to survive, and can only be occupied by one person per round, for thirty seconds before they are teleported out (you have the option to choose your destination if you decide to leave before the thirty seconds are up)

This was a map I worked on to give a slightly different aspect of gameplay to zombie mod servers. Most area's are either cadeable, good to hide, or good to fend off zombie hoards, but each one does have more then one entry or is vulnerable in some way. There are several breakable walls and floors, as well as windows and various other multiple entry ways. A code protected floodgate system for the basement areas as well as power generators where a console can be broken to shut down power to the whole complex (while enabling a few emergency lights and candles).


For those lazy folk out there, I've also generated the mp5navy and dual elites as your default weapons upon spawn, so you can go directly to your spots without the delay of buying weapons.

I made this map some months ago but I post it just today on Fpsbanana.




~~ The history ~~

A small suburb city has been invaded by a horde of Zombies, who bit all humans who they were able to find. Thanks to his secret labs, a famous scientist managed to survive a few weeks and captured some zombies to make experiences on them. But face to their number, he died tragically.
Now, special forces are coming to clean up the area and save the survivors. But are they also gonna be able to survive ??




~~ About the map ~~

This is a quite large map which may be played on a 64 players server. There is a lot of secrets which can't wait to be discovered. :D I'm talking about secret passages, secret rooms, secret explosions ... (clue: don't camp into the truck ! :D).
The map has been made for full ammo server, so there's a lot of camping spot. Some of them are easier to cover then other.
It is running for few months on this server : 91.191.158.2:27015 [FR]|FReZ|ZoMBiE MoD|UNLIMITED AMMO|FairPlay




~~ Other notes ~~

The map contains two models (a spider and a corpse) which have made by Elis (you might find them again here : http://s-low.info/forum/ ).
There are some other fun pictures which come from the french website Nioutaik ( http://www.nioutaik.fr/ ).
All the other credits come to the FReZ team ( http://frez.mondialservers.fr )




I hope you will find it nice and enjoy on it ! :D
